Project: AI College Application Assessment App Platform: iOS (Apple Store) Backend: Ollama (open-source LLM deployment), RAG or fine-tuning pipeline, ChromaDB (vector store), cloud hosting Extra: Web search capability, college/summer program recommendation logic

Sprint 1 (Week 1-2): Project Setup & Research
Goals:
* Define scope: what features the MVP must have (university/program matching, summer program suggestions, etc.).
* Set up development environment (iOS dev tools, backend cloud instance, GitHub repo, CI/CD basics).
* Install and test Ollama locally with chosen open-source LLM (e.g., LLaMA-3, Mistral).
* Stand up ChromaDB in cloud (AWS/GCP/Azure) for vector storage.
Deliverables:
* Architecture diagram (frontend, backend, vector DB, web search integration).
* Running Ollama model locally with sample Q&A.
* Cloud instance with ChromaDB accessible.
* GitHub repo initialized with base code + README.

Sprint 2 (Week 3-4): Data Ingestion & RAG Pipeline
Goals:
* Collect initial dataset: U.S. university programs, summer camps, admissions requirements (open data + scraping where allowed).
* Build preprocessing pipeline: clean text, chunking, embeddings, and store in ChromaDB.
* Integrate Ollama + ChromaDB for retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) queries.
Deliverables:
* Scripts to ingest and embed college/summer program data into ChromaDB.
* Working backend that answers queries with context from ChromaDB (e.g., “Which summer program fits a student interested in AI + music?”).
* Documented pipeline (data flow diagram + instructions).

Sprint 3 (Week 5-6): Backend API & Web Search
Goals:
* Wrap Ollama+ChromaDB in a backend API (FastAPI/Flask/Node).
* Add web search capability (e.g., SerpAPI, Tavily API, or Bing Search).
* Implement hybrid responses: structured recommendation (ranked list) + free-text reasoning.
Deliverables:
* Running backend API endpoint that takes a query and returns recommendations.
* Web search integrated with RAG pipeline.
* Unit tests for API endpoints.

Sprint 4 (Week 7-8): iOS App Frontend (MVP UI)
Goals:
* Build iOS SwiftUI app skeleton (Home, Search, Recommendation Results).
* Connect iOS frontend to backend API.
* Implement simple Q&A chat interface for user input.
Deliverables:
* Basic iOS app running on device/simulator.
* Working connection: user enters query → backend returns recommendations.
* Screenshots/demo video of MVP app flow.

Sprint 5 (Week 9-10): Personalization & Fine-Tuning
Goals:
* Add user profile support (basic inputs: GPA, interests, intended major, extracurriculars).
* Use profile info to tailor recommendations.
* Experiment with fine-tuning Ollama model on a small dataset of college admissions Q&A.
Deliverables:
* Working personalization flow (user profile stored in app or backend DB).
* Backend uses profile context in recommendation pipeline.
* Documented fine-tuning experiment with results (comparison vs. base model).

Sprint 6 (Week 11-12): Testing, Deployment & Store Prep
Goals:
* Perform QA testing (functional, usability, performance).
* Deploy backend to cloud (containerized with Docker + auto-restart).
* Prepare App Store submission (signing, TestFlight beta testing).
* Final intern presentation/demo.
Deliverables:
* Cloud-hosted backend accessible via API.
* Beta version of iOS app on TestFlight.
* Documentation: architecture, setup guide, user manual.
* Final demo presentation with app walk-through.

By the end of 3 months, you will have:
* A working iOS app MVP that recommends universities, programs, and summer camps.
* A backend system with Ollama, ChromaDB, and web search integrated.
* A documented pipeline for ingestion, retrieval, and recommendation.
* Beta-ready app for the Apple App Store.
